message: “They are commercially sexually exploited women in Kensington,” said Arielle Curry, Director of the anti-trafficking program. “The [home] is a place for them to recover and focus on themselves. They can get…connected with a case manager. We’ll give them support to help them on their goals — whether it’s a job, school, or medical appointments.”

data.description: The She’s My Sister ministry at Enon Tabernacle Baptist Church hosted their third annual Anti-Human Trafficking Awareness 5K Walk/Run on Oct. 7.
data.title: She's My Sister ministry hosts anti-human trafficking walk/run
